@SkillService_HostAddress = http://localhost:5212
@EmployeeService_HostAddress = http://localhost:5110

### ============================================
### SKILL MANAGEMENT
### ============================================

### Get All Skills
GET {{SkillService_HostAddress}}/skills
Accept: application/json

###

### Create a New Skill
POST {{SkillService_HostAddress}}/skills
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "skillName": "TypeScript"
}

###

### ============================================
### EMPLOYEE SKILL RATING
### ============================================

### Rate a Skill for an Employee
# Replace {employeeId} with actual GUID from EmployeeService
# Replace {skillId} with actual GUID from skills list (e.g., C# = 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111)
POST {{SkillService_HostAddress}}/employees/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/skills
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "skillId": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "rating": 4,
  "trainingNeeded": false
}

###

### ============================================
### SEARCH
### ============================================

### Search by Skill Name and Rating
GET {{SkillService_HostAddress}}/skills/search?skill=C%23&rating=3
Accept: application/json

###

### Search by Rating Only
GET {{SkillService_HostAddress}}/skills/search?rating=4
Accept: application/json

###

### Search by Skill Name Only
GET {{SkillService_HostAddress}}/skills/search?skill=Java
Accept: application/json

###

### ============================================
### EVENT FLOW TESTING
### ============================================

### Step 1: Create Employee in EmployeeService (triggers EmployeeCreatedEvent)
POST {{EmployeeService_HostAddress}}/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "role": "Software Engineer"
}

###
### Step 2: Check SkillService logs - should see EmployeeCreatedEvent consumed
### Step 3: Use the returned employeeId to rate skills above

